I would like to be able to use JIRA more effectively to track bug count vs. priority over time. This is a useful metric to show how the bug count is changing over time (growing, more serious bugs coming in, etc).

The current chart plugin will only let me go as far as a static pie chart for issue types by priority. This chart would ideally be a stacked bar chart configurable to look back over a period of time.

Currently, JIRA is unable to search for colons (:\) in the text fields of JIRA issues using JQL / simple search.

Double quoting a ':' in a JQL search or escaping it with a back-slash retrieves no results, even if the issues you're searching do have colons in the appropriate text fields.

Using a combination of double quoting and escaping doesn't work either - i.e. {{"\:"}}

