There is no documentation on the following RPC call:

http://docs.atlassian.com/software/jira/docs/api/rpc-jira-plugin/latest/com/atlassian/jira/rpc/soap/JiraSoapService.html#releaseVersion(java.lang.String,%20java.lang.String,%20com.atlassian.jira.rpc.soap.beans.RemoteVersion)

The name of the method seems to imply that calling it will release the version passed to it.  This is not the case, simply calling it will result in an error saying that the version can't be _unreleased_.  The method actually doesn't release the version, it changes the release state based on the argument passed to it, if "released" is set to true, it releases, if it's set to false, it unreleases.  At very least, the documentation should be updated to reflect this, better would be to rename the method to something that better describes it.

